When I was 8 or so my parent and stepabuser moved us to Texas. Not having resources or a plan they crashed on a friend's couch (with the two kids on the floor). He was the oddball friend from work to my stepabuser, I think.

He was late 20s or early 30s, just a tall gawky man with a horse laugh with a huge fantasy poster on his bedroom door. And was infinitely kinder than he should of been. Got quietly happy when I agreed to call him uncle. 1/

He was gay or bi, never asked him, but he dated guys and was sweet on this one blond. I don't even remember his boyfriends name anymore.

Both he and his boyfriend died from AIDS.

My parent & stepabuser abandoned him outside a hospital. Left him there with me in the fucking car. They'd knew, accepted him; but somehow this was 'wrong' all of a sudden.

Gods. A lot of people don't understand what the fuck the 70s & 80s were like for people. Especially the misfits and outcasts.
2/2

After dedicating my second run to minmaxing my stats for it, I have finally gotten the best possible outcome of the mercenary tribunal without savescumming!
All checks were a full 97% likely, my stat spread was 6 on H/E Coordination, 6 on Logic, 6 on Rhetoric, 6 on Authority, 7 on Suggestion, and 3 on Reaction Speed. I had every modifier for every red check open, the FT-500 thought, every piece of T-500 armor I could get equipped, and my weapon of choice was the Villiers 9mm I got from The Pigs. (Two bullets, I only used one)
The casualties on the union side were Theo, Angus, and Glen, which is the minimum, and the casualties on the mercs' side were all three of them, which is the maximum.
Kim survived, of course.
My initial spread for the run was 4/1/4/3, so I *really* worked hard to get Suggestion and Authority, it payed off, though!

The situation that started/caused my severe memory loss was ~10y ago at the point, and my ability to form new memories had a improved a ton over time but sometimes I definitely forget how much I still forget lol.

A minute ago my wife made an offhand mention of when I got my wisdom teeth out a few years ago and I was like ‚Äúno I have my wisdom teeth, I‚Äôve never had them removed!‚Äù and felt very confident in that face and was adamant I‚Äôve never had any dental surgery to the point she was doubting if she was misremembering something so we‚Äôre were trying to find some proof either way and after half an hour of looking still feeling fully 100% sure I suddenly remembered a joke she made about it at the time that wouldn‚Äôt make sense under any other circumstances and yup, I had my wisdom teeth taken out a few years ago. I even remember a bunch of related details from before and after now that I really try.

It like my brain was some jackass with a big fake smile saying ‚ÄúI know for sure X never happened and am offended you would even mention it as a possibility!‚Äù And then one tiny detail slipped through that made it clear X had to be true and my jackass brain put on a whole innocent act of saying ‚ÄúOh X?? X?? I thought you say Y, of course X is true! I would never say it wasn‚Äôt, in fact I have this big folder of records of X right here!‚Äù while it took the folder labeled X out of a giant dumpster with the word ‚Äòshred‚Äô on the side along with hundreds of other folders.

Because of how much far it‚Äôs come from it‚Äôs worst I tend to feel like at this point it‚Äôs not great but solidly within the range of ‚Äò‚Äônormal‚Äô for someone in the 20‚Äôs but then shit like this happens lmfao. üôÉ‚Äã
